#1:\r\n\r\nThere are 2 independent portions/aspects/changes/whatever to this fix:\r\n\r\n1. Modify the 'Add New Term' and 'Quick Add New Term' actions to take into account the status of the termbase. Both of these actions have a Condition attribute, which disables the entries in the menu if no text is selected in the open document. We need to extend this behavior to also check for write access, and if no access, then disable.\r\n\r\nThis means implementing a CompoundCondition, which joins the 'old' selection check to the new Termbase.IsReadOnly check, and returns true if there is text selected, AND the user has write-access to termbase.\r\n\r\n2. Retrieve the read-only status of the default termbase (Found! It already exists in ActiveDocument.TermbaseProvider.ActiveTermbase; we need to check for a ton of nulls, but it's there). Check how this is reported for a single-termbase provider (file-based, if read-only is possible) and for a multi-termbase provider (LC). be changed when target is edited)\r\n * lock - at target level (can be set on/off when target is edited)\r\n\r\nA segment exported with read only cannot be edited / unlocked in Studio.\r\n\r\nA segment exported with lock can be unlocked and edited in Studio.\r\n\r\nThe complete flow - export from Passolo + edit in Studio + import in Passolo will look like this:\r\n||Export from Passolo||Edit in Studio||Import in Passolo||\r\n|no lock|no lock, text changed|changed text|\r\n|read only|cannot be unlocked or edited|unchanged text|\r\n|locked|unlocked, text changed, locked|unchanged text|\r\n|locked|unlocked, text changed|unchanged text|\r\n|no lock|text changed, locked|unchanged Pereira Rojo","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"body":"Hi Stefan,\r\n\r\nThe table flow is correct. However 3 of the cases are a potential source of issues during the translation process:\r\n||Export from Passolo||Edit in Studio||Import in Passolo||\r\n\r\n|locked|unlocked, text changed, locked|unchanged text|\r\n|locked|unlocked, text changed|unchanged text|\r\n * During the translation or review process it might be necessary (as part of translation instructions) to unlock and modify segments in Studio (they can be then locked again or not). Currently, it is possible to unlock them but any changes won't be imported imported in Passolo. The string will remain locked and unchanged and no warning/error message displayed.  \r\n\r\n \r\n||Export from Passolo||Edit in Studio||Import in Passolo||\r\n|no lock|text changed, locked|unchanged text|\r\n * Again, sometimes translators will be requested to lock strings during translation process (ie: after a review process). If they do this now, the locked strings in Studio will not be imported/changed in Passolo.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBasically, we need Passolo to recognize the changes in Lock status and translated strings performed in Studio as these are a substantial part of the translation workflow. If a translator has to modified a locked string (and lock it again or not), Passolo should accept this and update the string and the lock status as required. If a string not locked in Passolo is translated and locked in Studio, Passolo should recognize this, update the string and the lock status as required.\r\n\r\nThanks!","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://jira.sdl.com/rest/api/2/user?username=epereirarojo","name":"epereirarojo","key":"epereirarojo","emailAddress":"epereirarojo@sdl.com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c3f4227f4f940bd5b2f3f18a9319ac95?d=mm&s=48","24x24":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c3f4227f4f940bd5b2f3f18a9319ac95?d=mm&s=24","16x16":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c3f4227f4f940bd5b2f3f18a9319ac95?d=mm&s=16","32x32":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c3f4227f4f940bd5b2f3f18a9319ac95?d=mm&s=32"},"displayName":"Enrique Pereira Rojo","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"created":"2019-04-23T09:23:38.673+0000","updated":"2019-04-23T09:23:38.673+0000"},{"self":"https://jira.sdl.com/rest/api/2/issue/459450/comment/649833","id":"649833","author":{"self":"https://jira.sdl.com/rest/api/2/user?username=dbrockmann","name":"dbrockmann","key":"dbrockmann","emailAddress":"dbrockmann@sdl.com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://jira.sdl.com/secure/useravatar?ownerId=dbrockmann&avatarId=12843","24x24":"https://jira.sdl.com/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=dbrockmann&avatarId=12843","16x16":"https://jira.sdl.com/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=dbrockmann&avatarId=12843","32x32":"https://jira.sdl.com/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=dbrockmann&avatarId=12843"},"displayName":"Daniel Brockmann","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"body":"Hi [~studorica], as discussed on email, we should introduce options so we don't enforce certain ways of working onto all users. The option for the first case could be called \"Update locked strings\" if that makes sense (and should be off by default)? We probably then also need a new dialog box for \"Import Options\" like we already have export options in the add-in setup. We could also add an option for the second case and could call it \"Update strings that have been locked outside Passolo\" (may need to tweak this but can serve as an initial idea for the option name). This could be two check boxes so users can decide for both cases individually?\r\n\r\nLet me know if this works or if we should have another conversation - happy to jump on a call on Skype anytime.
